1
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:50,333
[NARRATOR]
The Earth Union Fleet


2
00:00:50,416 --> 00:00:52,958
was suddenly caught
in a desperate battle.


3
00:00:54,416 --> 00:00:55,750
[VULGAR grunts]

4
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:57,375
[OPERATOR 13A] Three craft
damaged in Vulgar's unit!

5
00:00:57,458 --> 00:00:58,875
Sending for help!

6
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:01,000
[NARRATOR] They had been
attacked by the People of Metus

7
00:01:01,083 --> 00:01:04,833
who trapped them dangerously
close to the atmosphere.

8
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:08,291
[MECHANIC 13A]
Let's go people! Sortie time!

9
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:09,500
[LIGIER]
You ready?

10
00:01:09,583 --> 00:01:11,625
I need you back in four
minutes at the most.

11
00:01:11,708 --> 00:01:13,416
I know you think your
Durandal's awesome,

12
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:16,083
but even it won't withstand
the atmosphere.

13
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:18,583
[SUBARU] No you're right,
it's been sucking lately.

14
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:20,541
And I'm a pretty hot mess, too.

15
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:22,666
Who cares if we don't come back.

16
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:25,166
Here! New helmets
make everything better.

17
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:27,500
[gasps] For real?

18
00:01:27,583 --> 00:01:29,375
Yours was looking
a little tragic.

19
00:01:29,458 --> 00:01:32,208
Plus, I know that you hated that
Shigeko wrote your name on it.

20
00:01:32,291 --> 00:01:34,333
You get me.

21
00:01:34,416 --> 00:01:37,208
And PS...

22
00:01:37,291 --> 00:01:38,958
You shouldn't let the fact
that the Durandal

23
00:01:39,041 --> 00:01:42,708
is down affect how
you perform, ya know?

24
00:01:42,791 --> 00:01:45,875
I hate to say it, but I need
you to help us, Subaru.

25
00:01:45,958 --> 00:01:47,916
You're our only hope right now.

26
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,625
[SUBARU]
Y-Yeah, sounds great.

27
00:01:49,708 --> 00:01:51,458
Okay, awesome. Good talk.

28
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:54,166
You can pay me back
for the helmet later!

29
00:01:58,541 --> 00:02:00,166
[NARRATOR]
It's really that simple.

30
00:02:00,250 --> 00:02:02,666
Having reawakened his
inner warrior thanks to

31
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:05,541
a droplet of attention
from a gorgeous female,

32
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:09,250
Subaru placed a protective
film on his new visor.

33
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:11,208
Sucks putting these things
on a round surface

34
00:02:11,291 --> 00:02:14,750
when you only get one chance.
And they're so damn expensive.

35
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:17,000
[PAC2-AR] Subaru, the enemy
is quickly approaching.

36
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:18,500
We need to focus and be ready!

37
00:02:18,583 --> 00:02:21,541
<i>"Primero use la tela</i>
<i>provista para--"</i>

38
00:02:21,625 --> 00:02:22,791
What?

39
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:24,541
[PAC2-AR] Or I guess we
could just wait to die.

40
00:02:24,625 --> 00:02:25,958
It's whatever.

41
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:31,375
[PAC2-AR yelps]
Random acts of nakedness?!

42
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:33,958
Oh, so because he doesn't want
to get lint on his helmet,

43
00:02:34,041 --> 00:02:36,083
I have to get visually harassed.

44
00:02:36,166 --> 00:02:38,166
This level of obsession
with protective film

45
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:39,625
can't be considered normal!

46
00:02:39,708 --> 00:02:40,916
[beeping]

47
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,333
[PAC2-AR]
Subaru! Incoming enemy!

48
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:45,458
[SUBARU B laughing]

49
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:46,791
[SUBARU gasps]

50
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:50,833
[gasps]

51
00:02:50,916 --> 00:02:52,625
[SUBARU] Are those bubbles
underneath the film?!

52
00:02:52,708 --> 00:02:55,500
Three of them?!
Oh, come on!

53
00:02:58,208 --> 00:03:01,083
Hey, Soob. This is
called checkmate.

54
00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:02,750
Oh, it's you.

55
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:05,500
[ISUZU] The Kerukeion
will hold him in place!

56
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:07,875
But I need you to kill him!

57
00:03:07,958 --> 00:03:10,708
Hmph. Hm...?

58
00:03:12,375 --> 00:03:15,250
[ISUZU] That is not a tear
in my favorite suit!

59
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:18,250
Okay, I need a minute.
Sorry, Subaru B!

60
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:21,250
You are not getting out of
this that easily. I will--

61
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:22,333
[gasps]

62
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:26,875
[SUBARU] Is that a cockpit mite
in one of the bubbles?!

63
00:03:26,958 --> 00:03:28,666
[screaming]

64
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,708
Huh?

65
00:03:34,708 --> 00:03:37,000
The Durandal can't
decelerate, Sir!

66
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:38,375
It's about to reenter
the atmosphere!

67
00:03:38,458 --> 00:03:39,833
--[LIGIER gasps]
--[VULGAR] Hm?

68
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,500
Ah! Balls!

69
00:03:44,583 --> 00:03:47,250
Why won't you just stay stiff
long enough to get in the hole?

70
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:48,750
[OPERATOR 13C]
Update! It's in reentry!


71
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:49,666
[BOTH gasp]

72
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,041
What are you doing?!

73
00:03:51,125 --> 00:03:53,166
Stop messing around
and come back!

74
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:54,708
[SUBARU yelling]

75
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:57,083
[NARRATOR] One pilot trying
to rip off a protective film.


76
00:03:57,166 --> 00:04:00,000
Another fighting against
odds to thread a needle.

77
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:03,250
Two men bound by fate,
plunging into G force!

78
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:09,083
We've lost contact!
It doesn't look good.

79
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:11,291
[ALL gaps]

80
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,958
His dumb mecha can't
handle that atmosphere.

81
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:15,750
Good one, Pee Pants.

82
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,125
What the--?

83
00:04:17,208 --> 00:04:18,750
When'd I reenter the atmosphere?

84
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:21,125
Hey Soob, guess what? Overtime.

85
00:04:21,208 --> 00:04:23,916
Neither one of us will
survive at this rate.

86
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,541
I'll use my Griffin Mode.

87
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:28,125
It'll stabilize our
angle of incidence.

88
00:04:28,208 --> 00:04:30,000
Hurry and launch
your escape pod.

89
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:32,125
I'll catch you. I promise.

90
00:04:38,083 --> 00:04:40,708
[ISUZU]
Subaru? Hey, can you hear me?

91
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:42,916
He's unconscious.

92
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,208
So be it.

93
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:46,375
It is a battlefield.

94
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:47,958
Farewell.

95
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:50,875
What a drama queen, going out
in a blaze of glory like that.

96
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,416
[PAC2-AR]
We are running out of time!

97
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,125
If we don't evacuate now,
we could die in here--

98
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:56,125
Shut up! I know!

99
00:04:56,208 --> 00:04:59,000
But I can't just leave the
Durandal to save myself!

100
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,458
Now, let me finish!

101
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,125
I'm typing as fast as I can.

102
00:05:02,208 --> 00:05:04,458
[NARRATOR] In desperate
situations such as these,

103
00:05:04,541 --> 00:05:08,250
Subaru turns to the internet
for council and guidance.

104
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:10,541
Done! And I did it
without jokes.

105
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:12,625
That way they know I'm serious!

106
00:05:12,708 --> 00:05:13,916
Submit!

107
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:18,458
--[computer pings]
--[PAC2-AR gasps]

108
00:05:18,541 --> 00:05:20,041
[SUBARU]
Yes! So many answers!

109
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:22,000
[SUBARU gasps]

110
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:26,333
[SUBARU] "LOL"?! But I
didn't use any smilies!

111
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:27,791
What's wrong with people?!

112
00:05:27,875 --> 00:05:29,083
Screw them!

113
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:31,250
How do they not recognize
a man with a crisis?

114
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:32,708
Ow!

115
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:35,583
[PAC2-AR] Armor temperature
has reached 2,000 degrees!

116
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:37,333
The escape lever
is under your seat!

117
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:39,416
Pull it, Subaru! Hurry! Please!

118
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:42,583
I feel dizzy. Sleepy.

119
00:05:43,125 --> 00:05:44,583
[SUBARU]
You're so strong!

120
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:46,375
[DURANDAL]
As are you.

121
00:05:46,458 --> 00:05:48,083
[SUBARU]
My boss sucks, amiright?

122
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,125
[DURANDAL]
Believe me, I know.

123
00:05:50,208 --> 00:05:51,958
[NARRATOR]
While the cockpit was broiling,

124
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:55,041
Subaru reflected on his
memories with the Durandal--

125
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:59,000
which were actually disturbing
fantasies that never happened.

126
00:05:59,083 --> 00:06:00,291
[SUBARU]
Is this it?

127
00:06:00,375 --> 00:06:02,750
Are we going to die?

128
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:05,541
[gasps] I don't wanna!

129
00:06:05,625 --> 00:06:07,250
Not now!

130
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:09,458
I'm sorry! Forgive me, Durandal!

131
00:06:09,541 --> 00:06:11,458
It's just... I can't die yet.

132
00:06:11,541 --> 00:06:16,125
The Earth still needs me,
but I love you! [growls]

133
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:21,916
[SUBARU] Come on! Why is this
lever so hard to pull?!

134
00:06:35,458 --> 00:06:37,625
[SUBARU]
The familiar embrace of gravity.

135
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:39,750
I'm on the ground.

136
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:43,708
I guess this means
I didn't die up there.

137
00:06:43,791 --> 00:06:46,333
It was you.

138
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:49,500
You protected me.

139
00:06:49,583 --> 00:06:51,666
Thanks, Durandal.

140
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:55,500
[SUBARU whimpers]

141
00:06:55,583 --> 00:07:02,375
[SUBARU sobs]

